cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with generative modelling and the use of neural networks to approximate the Wasserstein metric. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as generative models are often used in image generation tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as generative models are a popular area of research in AI. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the evaluation of generative models, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
